- Use idiomatic Elixir. Follow the [Elixir Style Guide](https://github.com/christopheradams/elixir_style_guide).
- Use `@doc` and `@spec` for all public context functions.
- Prefer pattern matching in function signatures over `if/else` or `case` inside functions when possible.
- Use `with` for complex multi-step operations that can fail.
